{"type":"message","id":"92ce1fdb","parentId":"1eba0e73","timestamp":"2026-03-24T12:29:43.971Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_yqhmcwkib4ca_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 082815\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and decide on the next concrete action.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked COMPLETE\r\n2. The key pending action is the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) Experiment\r\n3. Next action items listed:\r\n   - Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n   - Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n   - Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n   - Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nThe most impactful single action would be to start implementing the TIC classifier. I should create a script or module that:\r\n1. Reads the pulse logs\r\n2. Classifies content as invariant or variant\r\n3. Measures classification accuracy\r\n4. Attempts next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nLet me look at what files exist and what would be the best first step. I should implement the TIC classifier as a Python script that can process the pulse logs.\r\n\r\nThe doc `research/COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md` should contain the theoretical basis for this experiment.\r\n\r\nLet me create a TIC classifier script that:\r\n1. Loads pulse logs\r\n2. Implements basic invariance detection (comparing content across pulses)\r\n3. Classifies as invariant/variant\r\n4. Attempts prediction\r\n\r\nThis is a concrete, file-edit action that advances the goals.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the critical next step to validate the compression-causal duality hypothesis. I need to implement the classifier that will process pulse logs and measure invariant/variant classification accuracy.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `tic/classifier.py` - the core TIC classifier that reads pulse logs, detects invariant vs variant patterns, and attempts next-pulse prediction. This is the foundational implementation for the Phase 1-2 unified experiment.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n`\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: \"\"\"\r\nTemporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\nTests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure.\r\n\r\nSuccess criteria:\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom typing import List, Dict, Tuple, Set\r\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass\r\nfrom collections import defaultdict\r\n\r\n@dataclass\r\nclass PulseLog:\r\n    timestamp: str\r\n    path: Path\r\n    content: str\r\n    lines: List[str]\r\n\r\nclass TICClassifier:\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Temporal Invariance Compression classifier.\r\n    \r\n    Invariant patterns = structure that persists across pulses (causal)\r\n    Variant patterns = content unique to specific pulses (accidental)\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    \r\n    def __init__(self, logs_dir: Path):\r\n        self.logs_dir = logs_dir\r\n        self.pulses: List[PulseLog] = []\r\n        self.invariant_patterns: Set[str] = set()\r\n        self.variant_patterns: Set[str] = set()\r\n        \r\n    def load_pulses(self, limit: int = 20) -> List[PulseLog]:\r\n        \"\"\"Load pulse log files, most recent first.\"\"\"\r\n        log_files = sorted(self.logs_dir.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"), reverse=True)[:limit]\r\n        \r\n        for log_file in log_files:\r\n            content = log_file.read_text()\r\n            self.pulses.append(PulseLog(\r\n                timestamp=log_file.stem.replace(\"pulse_\", \"\"),\r\n                path=log_file,\r\n                content=content,\r\n                lines=content.split('\\n')\r\n            ))\r\n        \r\n        return self.pulses\r\n    \r\n    def extract_tokens(self, text: str) -> Set[str]:\r\n        \"\"\"Extract meaningful tokens from text.\"\"\"\r\n        # Remove code blocks, markdown syntax\r\n        text = re.sub(r'```[\\s\\S]*?```', ' ', text)\r\n        text = re.sub(r'`[^`]+`', ' ', text)\r\n        text = re.sub(r'[#*_\\[\\]\\(\\)]', ' ', text)\r\n        # Extract words\r\n        words = re.findall(r'\\b[a-zA-Z][a-zA-Z0-9_]+\\b', text.lower())\r\n        return set(words)\r\n    \r\n    def detect_invariants(self) -> Dict[str, float]:\r\n        \"\"\"\r\n        Detect patterns that persist across pulses.\r\n        Returns dict of pattern -> persistence ratio\r\n        \"\"\"\r\n        if len(self.pulses) < 2:\r\n            return {}\r\n        \r\n        pattern_counts = defaultdict(int)\r\n        \r\n        for pulse in self.pulses:\r\n            tokens = self.extract_tokens(pulse.content)\r\n            for token in tokens:\r\n                pattern_counts[token] += 1\r\n        \r\n        n_pulses = len(self.pulses)\r\n        invariance_scores = {}\r\n        \r\n        for pattern, count in pattern_counts.items():\r\n            ratio = count / n_pulses\r\n            if ratio >= 0.5:  # Appears in >50% of pulses = invariant\r\n                invariance_scores[pattern] = ratio\r\n                self.invariant_patterns.add(pattern)\r\n            else:\r\n                self.variant_patterns.add(pattern)\r\n        \r\n        return invariance_scores\r\n    \r\n    def classify_content(self, content: str) -> Tuple[Set[str], Set[str]]:\r\n        \"\"\"Classify content tokens as invariant or variant.\"\"\"\r\n        tokens = self.extract_tokens(content)\r\n        \r\n        invariants = tokens & self.invariant_patterns\r\n        variants = tokens - self.invariant_patterns\r\n        \r\n        return invariants, variants\r\n    \r\n    def predict_next_pulse(self, current_pulse: PulseLog) -> Set[str]:\r\n        \"\"\"\r\n        Predict tokens likely in next pulse based on invariant patterns.\r\n        Uses invariant patterns as the causal structure.\r\n        \"\"\"\r\n        current_tokens = self.extract_tokens(current_pulse.content)\r\n        invariants_in_current = current_tokens & self.invariant_patterns\r\n        \r\n        # Next pulse should contain invariants from current pulse\r\n        predicted = invariants_in_current.copy()\r\n        \r\n        # Add high-frequency invariants\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 0\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 08:28:44\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774355383969}}
